{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job: How Can I Contend with God?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Job answered:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Yes, I know that it is so, but how can a mortal be righteous before God?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If one wished to contend with God,[^11] he could not answer Him one time out of a thousand."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "God is wise in heart and mighty in strength. Who has resisted Him and prospered?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He moves mountains without their knowledge and overturns them in His anger."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He shakes the earth from its place, so that its foundations tremble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He commands the sun not to shine;[^12] He seals off the stars."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He alone stretches out the heavens and treads on the waves of the sea."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He is the Maker of the Bear and Orion, of the Pleiades and the constellations of the south."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He does great things beyond searching out, and wonders without number."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Were He to pass by me, I would not see Him; were He to move, I would not recognize Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If He takes away,[^13] who can stop Him? Who dares to ask Him, ‘What are You doing?’"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "God does not restrain His anger; the helpers of Rahab cower beneath Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "How then can I answer Himor choose my arguments against Him?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For even if I were right, I could not answer. I could only beg my Judge for mercy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If I summoned Him and He answered me, I do not believe He would listen to my voice."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For He would crush me with a tempest and multiply my wounds without cause."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He does not let me catch my breath, but overwhelms me with bitterness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If it is a matter of strength, He is indeed mighty! If it is a matter of justice, who can summon Him[^14]?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even if I were righteous, my mouth would condemn me; if I were blameless, it would declare me guilty.[^15]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though I am blameless, I have no concern for myself; I despise my own life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is all the same, and so I say,‘He destroys both the blameless and the wicked.’"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When the scourge brings sudden death, He mocks the despair of the innocent."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked; He blindfolds its judges.\nIf it is not He, then who is it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My days are swifter than a runner; they flee without seeing good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They sweep by like boats of papyrus, like an eagle swooping down on its prey."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If I were to say, ‘I will forget my complaint and change my expression and smile,’"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I would still dread all my sufferings; I know that You will not acquit me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Since I am already found guilty, why should I labor in vain?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If I should wash myself with snow[^16] and cleanse my hands with lye,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "then You would plunge me into the pit, and even my own clothes would despise me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For He is not a man like me, that I can answer Him, that we can take each other to court."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Nor is there a mediator between us, to lay his hand upon us both."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let Him remove His rod from me, so that His terror will no longer frighten me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then I would speak without fear of Him. But as it is, I am on my own."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}